meanings.definition: To surpass in avoiding bad luck or misfortune.
meanings.sent1: She always manages to outjinxing any potential bad luck.
meanings.sent2: He believes in outjinxing by carrying a lucky charm everywhere.
meanings.sent3: By outjinxing the black cat, she felt invincible.
meanings.sent4: Outjinxing the curse, he walked away unscathed.
meanings.sent5: Outjinxing the storm, she arrived home dry and safe.

meanings.definition: To outdo in avoiding a jinx or curse.
meanings.sent1: They have a competition to see who can outjinxing the curse first.
meanings.sent2: She is known for outjinxing any jinx that comes her way.
meanings.sent3: Outjinxing the broken mirror, he laughed at superstitions.
meanings.sent4: By outjinxing the spell, she broke free from its hold.
meanings.sent5: Outjinxing the hex, he proved that luck was on his side.
